LINE.Text: Random forest algorithms improve the accuracy of decision trees by using multiple trees
with randomly selected subsets of data. This example reviews the expression levels of
various genes associated with breast cancer relapse and computes a relapse risk.
Each neuron in any neural network converts many inputs into single outputs via one or more
hidden layers. Recurrent neural networks [RNNs] additionally pass values from step to step,
making step-by-step learning possible. In other words, RNNs have a form of memory,
allowing previous outputs to affect subsequent inputs.
